The loop is not correct.  For starters instead of this while loop

    while (sPtr != NULL || value != (*sPtr)-&gt;data)

there should be the following loop

    while ( *sPtr != NULL &amp;&amp; value != (*sPtr)-&gt;data)

This statement

        *sPtr = (*sPtr)-&gt;nextPtr;

changes your list.

The function can look the following way

    int find( ListNode **sPtr, char value )
    {
        int count = 0;
    
        while ( *sPtr != NULL &amp;&amp; value != (*sPtr)-&gt;data )
        {
            count++;
            sPtr = &amp;(*sPtr)-&gt;nextPtr;
        }
    
        return *sPtr == NULL ? - 1 : count;
    }

That is node positions start from 0. If a node with the given value is not found the function returns -1.

In fact as the list is not changed in the function the first parameter may be declare as a single pointer. In this case the function can look like

    int find( ListNode *sPtr, char value )
    {
        int count = 0;
    
        while ( sPtr != NULL &amp;&amp; value != sPtr-&gt;data )
        {
            count++;
            sPtr = sPtr-&gt;nextPtr;
        }
    
        return sPtr == NULL ? - 1 : count;
    }

