The easiest fix is to simply notify the adapter each time that you add a hotel to the list:

    reference1.addListenerForSingleValueEvent(new ValueEventListener() {
        @Override
        public void onDataChange(@NonNull DataSnapshot dataSnapshot) {
            Hotel hotel=dataSnapshot.getValue(Hotel.class);
            hotels.add(hotel);
            adapter.notifyDataSetChanged()
        }

        @Override
        public void onCancelled(@NonNull DatabaseError databaseError) {
            throw databaseError.toException();
        }
    });

I made a few more changes here:

* Use `addListenerForSingleValueEvent`, so that we don&#39;t keep the listener attached. With your original code, if you made a change to the hotel in the database, a second copy of that hotel would be added to the list.
* Don&#39;t leave `onCancelled` empty, as you may be hiding important error messages there. I implemented it in the simplest way possible here.

